g.text: High-level overview of the Federated Data Architecture for the Immunization Record Gateway (IRG) Project

g.id: 'box "Federated Data Architecture for IRG Project"'.Data Sources

text.tspan: Sources include various health data systems from across provinces, territories, and federal agencies. These sources provide immunization records and related health data that are critical for national-level analytics and decision-making.

g.id: 'box "Federated Data Architecture for IRG Project"'.Access Control Gateway

text.tspan: Responsible for enforcing data governance policies, including access controls, data anonymization, and transformation. The ACG ensures that sensitive patient data is protected and compliant with privacy regulations before it is shared or analyzed.

g.id: 'box "Federated Data Architecture for IRG Project"'.Kafka Stream

text.tspan: Enables real-time data streaming between components. Kafka handles the continuous ingestion of data from the ACG, ensuring that the most up-to-date information is available for analysis in downstream systems like Neo4j.

Stores and models complex relationships within the immunization data. Neo4j allows for advanced queries and analytics, such as tracking vaccine distribution networks, identifying clusters of unvaccinated individuals, and understanding the spread of diseases.

Built on Neo4j, Neodash provides dynamic visualization capabilities, allowing users to explore graph data interactively. This tool is essential for visualizing relationships within the data, such as connections between patients, vaccines, and healthcare providers.

g.id: 'box "Federated Data Architecture for IRG Project"'.Visualization Layer

text.tspan: Traditional business intelligence tools like Power BI and Tableau are integrated to create dashboards and reports. These tools pull data from Neo4j to present insights on immunization coverage, trends, and other key metrics.

g.id: 'box "Federated Data Architecture for IRG Project"'.Visualization Layer.Power BI

text.tspan: Microsoft's business analytics tool, used to create interactive dashboards and reports that visualize immunization data.

g.id: 'box "Federated Data Architecture for IRG Project"'.Visualization Layer.Tableau

text.tspan: A leading data visualization tool that allows for intuitive, drag-and-drop analytics, making it easy to create sophisticated visualizations of immunization data.
